<P>M'FINGAL. A MODERN EPIC POEM, IN FOUR CANTOS.</P>
<Q><L>Ergo non &s;atis e&s;t ri&s;u diducere rictum</L>
<L>Auditoris: et e&s;t quaedam tamen hic quoque virtus.</L>
<L>E&s;t brevitate opus, ut currat &s;ententia, neu &s;e</L>
<L>Imp<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">diat verbis <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> onerantibus aures.</L>
<L>Et &s;e<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">m me opus e&s;t modo tri&s;ti, &s;oepe joco&s;o,</L>
<L>Defe<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">ente vicem modo Rhetoris, atque Poetae,</L>
<L><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> parcentis vi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ibus atque</L>
<L>Extenuantis eas con&s;ulto. Ridiculum acri</L>
<L>Fortias et melius magnas ple<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">u<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">nque &s;ecat res.</L>
<BIBL>Horat. Lib. I. Sat. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"></BIBL></Q>
<P><HI>HARTFORD:</HI> Printed by HUDSON and GOODWIN, near the Great Bridge, 1782.</P>
